(27114, 'caffeine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Therefore, an increase in the metabolism of coadministered CYP1A2 substrates (e.g., theophylline, caffeine) or CYP3A4 substrates (e.g., midazolam, testosterone) is not anticipated.', 'DailyMed'),
